    <body>
      <head>Walther Davisson</head>
      <div>

        <p>German violinist, orchestral conductor, and teacher.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p>Walther Davisson studied violin at the Hoch Conservatory in Frankfurt 1900–06. He was
          second violin in the Rebner Quartet early in his career, and was an orchestral conductor,
          some of whose chamber, solo, and orchestral recordings still exist.</p>

        <p>Having been Deputy Director to <ref cRef="entity-000659">Max von Pauer</ref> at the <ref
            cRef="entity-002872">Leipzig Conservatory</ref>, he served as its Director from 1932 to
          1942, and artistic director of the Frankfurt Hochschule and Hoch Conservatory 1950–54.</p>
      </div>

    </body>

